column11: Three males were returnees from Italy and Kuwait while the female was a family member of a foreign returnee
Two male cases are returnees from Italy and the female is a family member

First death from community transmission[122] *Government press releases from both 2020-3-20 and 2020-3-21 state that 'total number of individuals tested for COVID-19 till date' is 433 and 'number tested in last 24 hours' is 36. These are likely errors.
New cases include a doctor who treated the patient who died on 20 March.[123]
New cases characteristics: 3 males, 3 females; 23 healthcare workers, and two returnees from India and Bahrain. New death caused by community transmission.
New positives include returnee from Saudi Arabia and 4 locals with epidemiological link. The death of the female was related to community transmission
The total number of recoveries surged and crossed 1,000 marks, according to new guidelines.
The total number of coronavirus cases in Bangladesh exceeded the total number of coronavirus cases in China.

Bangladesh saw a sharp surge in the total number of recoveries two days after overtaking China in terms of coronavirus infections. Dr. Nasima Sultana said that over 15,000 patients recovered from COVID-19. The patients who recovered from COVID-19 included both symptomatic and asymptomatic patients. The recoveries occurred not only in hospital, but also at home.
The total number of coronavirus cases in Bangladesh exceeded the total number of coronavirus cases in France. In terms of the number of recoveries, Bangladesh also overtook France.
Bangladesh overtook China in terms of the number of recoveries.
The number of recoveries in Bangladesh exceeded the number of active cases.
